CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 27, 1952, pg. 10 reads: "Alpha Kappa Alpha Debs - Readying for the Jan 5 Debutante Cotillion, given annually by members of Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, are these charming and pretty young misses who'll make their bow at Syria Mosque before relatives and friends on that gala evening. Left to right, on floor: Mary Pettus, Gladys Moors, Burnistine McClaney, Guerelan Smith, Diane E. Casey, Willa A. Rogers, Marlene B. Harris, Rosalind Cobbs and Geraldine Harris.  Second row: Joanne Snyder, Elizabeth Patterson, Celestine Pryor, Evelyn Hawkins, Betty Scott, Florence Anderson, Barbara Pryor, Batty LaVerne Smith, Brenadean Pressley, Georgia Marie Drysdale, Miriam Jacobs and Harriet Wildes. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Alpha Kappa Alpha members first row, from left: Mary Pettus, Gladys Moore, Burnistine McClaney, Guerelan Smith, Diane E. Casey, Willa A. Rogers, Marlene B. Harris, Rosalind Cobbs, and Geraldine Harris; second row: Joanne Snyder, Elizabeth Patterson, Celestine Pryor, Evelyn Hawkins, Betty Scott, Florence Anderson, Barbara Pryor, Batty LaVerne Smith, Brenadean Pressley, Georgia Marie Drysdale, Miriam Jacobs, and Harriet Wildes, gathered in interior with squiggle patterned curtains
